sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / kubectl
    participant APIServer as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Kueue Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Controller as Kueue Controller<br/>Manager
    participant Scheduler as Kueue Admission<br/>Scheduler
    participant Cache as In-Memory<br/>Quota Cache

    Note over User,Cache: Flow 1: Job Admission

    User->>APIServer: POST Job (batch/v1)<br/>Auth: User credentials
    APIServer->>Webhook: POST /mutate-batch-v1-job<br/>Auth: API Server client cert
    Webhook->>Webhook: Default queue-name label<br/>Set suspend=true<br/>Lossless defaulting
    Webhook-->>APIServer: Mutated Job
    APIServer->>Webhook: POST /validate-batch-v1-job<br/>Auth: API Server client cert
    Webhook->>Webhook: Validate queue-name immutability
    Webhook-->>APIServer: Admission Response

    Note over Controller,Cache: Workload Creation & Scheduling

    Controller->>APIServer: Watch Jobs<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    APIServer-->>Controller: Job Created Event
    Controller->>APIServer: Create Workload CR<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>Cache: Update queue state

    Scheduler->>Cache: Check pending workloads
    Cache-->>Scheduler: Pending workload list
    Scheduler->>Cache: Check ClusterQueue quotas<br/>& ResourceFlavor assignment
    Cache-->>Scheduler: Quota available

    Scheduler->>APIServer: Update Workload status<br/>(Admitted=true, flavors assigned)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>APIServer: Unsuspend Job<br/>(set suspend=false)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    APIServer-->>User: Job pods created

    Note over User,Cache: Flow 2: MultiKueue Distribution

    participant RemoteAPI as Remote K8s API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+

    Controller->>APIServer: Watch Workloads<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    APIServer-->>Controller: Workload admitted to<br/>MultiKueue ClusterQueue

    Controller->>RemoteAPI: Create remote Workload + Job<br/>Auth: kubeconfig credentials
    RemoteAPI-->>Controller: Remote workload created
    Controller->>RemoteAPI: Watch remote Workload status<br/>Auth: kubeconfig credentials
    RemoteAPI-->>Controller: Remote workload completed
    Controller->>APIServer: Update local Workload status<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token

    Note over User,Cache: Flow 3: Provisioning Request

    Scheduler->>Cache: Check quota - insufficient nodes
    Scheduler->>APIServer: Create ProvisioningRequest CR<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token

    participant Autoscaler as Cluster Autoscaler

    Autoscaler->>APIServer: Watch ProvisioningRequests<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    APIServer-->>Autoscaler: New ProvisioningRequest
    Autoscaler->>Autoscaler: Provision nodes
    Autoscaler->>APIServer: Update ProvisioningRequest status<br/>(Provisioned=true)
    Controller->>APIServer: Watch ProvisioningRequest status
    APIServer-->>Controller: Nodes provisioned
    Controller->>APIServer: Update AdmissionCheck<br/>(Ready=true)
    Scheduler->>APIServer: Admit Workload
